DIGEST
SB 230 Original 2026 Regular Session Barrow
Proposed constitutional amendment establishes a livable wage that every employer will be
required to pay each employee. Proposed constitutional amendment sets the state livable
hourly wage rate at $10.25. Proposed constitutional amendment provides an effective date
of January 1, 2027.
Proposed constitutional amendment provides that the state livable wage rate will be
increased by rate of inflation for the 12-month period prior to that September according to
the Consumer Price Index or its successor index.
Proposed constitutional amendment provides exceptions for employers whose employees
are tipped employees, family members, or mental or physically disabled.
Specifies submission of the amendment to the voters at the statewide election to be held on
November 3, 2026.
(Adds Const. Art. XII, Sec. 18)
